<ns3379:section xmlns:ns3379="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.platforms.linux.networkServices.sendmail.sendmail">

	<ns3380:title xmlns:ns3380="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Mail server using Sendmail</ns3380:title>
	<ns3381:para xmlns:ns3381="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	Sendmail is a feature-rich mail server, yet is has achieved the status of being difficult to administer. Only a very basic configuration of sendmail is covered in this section.
	</ns3381:para>
	<ns3382:para xmlns:ns3382="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
	For alternatives to sendmail, have a look at qmail or exim, which are supposed to provide simpler configuration.
	</ns3382:para>
